text: your code is valuable as your
application's codebase grows and your
development team gets larger finding a
highly available and secure way to store
and version code can become difficult
and costly wouldn't it be nice if you
could just focus on securely developing
apps and not have to worry about
managing and scaling your Source control
system better yet what if you could do
all of this while continuing to use your
existing git tools introducing AWS code
commit a fully manage Source control
service in the cloud that makes it easy
for companies to host secure highly
scalable private G repositories code
commit eliminates the need to set up
manage and scale your own source control
system there is no Hardware to manage or
software to patch an update and you
don't have to worry about running out of
space code commit is built on a highly
redundant and durable architecture
keeping your repositories highly
available and accessible as your project
grows and the number and size of your
repositories increases code commit
automatically scales so you never run
out of space with code commit you can
store code binaries images and libraries
and more AWS code commit automatically
encrypts your files in transit and at
rest so you don't have to worry about
your code's privacy and security code
commit works with your existing get
tools and offers extensibility through
web hooks that integrate with your
existing processes this lets you trigger
AWS Lambda functions or push
notifications such as as SMS or email in
response to events in your repositories
code commit is integrated with AWS
identity and access management allowing
you to assign user specific permissions
to your repositories so that you can
control and monitor who can access your
data as well as how when and where they
can access it code commit works with
your existing git graphical clients and
tools this allows you to use your
existing development environment plugins
continuous integration and continuous
Delivery Systems and graphical clients
with code commit
with AWS code commit you pay per active
user per month if needed extra storage
and get requests are available at
additional charge there are no upfront
fees and no setup costs get started on
AWS code commit with a few clicks in the
AWS Management console
